missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/mission-context.md:851:Chain 03 is honest and useful, but it is still more likely to produce a calibrated obstruction memo than a live route. Its positive path remains narrow because every candidate has to survive nonlocal pressure-Hessian debt, representation stability, eigenvalue degeneracy, and prior-art adjacency all at once. That makes it a good negative-discovery branch, but a weaker final choice than Chain 02.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:31:Step 3 is built to strip away gains that are "really" geometric or pressure-tensor effects. That is good if the goal is a pure reformulation result. It is bad if the only real NS-specific cancellations are hybrid: exact algebraic form plus alignment, or rewrite plus concentrated tube geometry, or rewrite plus tensor structure. The chain risks discarding the only live mechanisms because they are not pure enough.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:79:- "Survive modest perturbation away from special alignment" is not operationally defined. Perturbation in what norm, on what scale, and relative to which localization? A cancellation can look robust or fragile depending on the metric.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:80:- The contamination screen comes after Step 2 instead of being integrated into it. Given the mission context, fragility to alignment and branch-mixing are not afterthoughts; they are central facts. Waiting until Step 3 means Step 2 may already have overinvested in a mirage.
