missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:5:This is a more honest version of the tensor-alignment instinct than most. It explicitly names the full stretching term, it brings harmonic far-field debt into the chain instead of hiding it, and it gives the negative branch real status.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:15:- The representation package is not the main unresolved choice. The real unresolved choice is the theorem-level endpoint. "Full stretching control," "pressure-Hessian/strain defect control," and "harmonic-moment cancellation" are not three versions of one bottleneck; they are three different proof architectures.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:26:- The candidate menu is crowded with familiar descendants of the alignment and restricted-Euler literature: eigenvalue-gap combinations, vorticity-to-eigenframe alignment, pressure/strain misalignment, and defect observables. A table can make these look newly systematized without making them new.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:50:- Many pressure-Hessian identities are NS-specific in algebraic form while still being non-coercive analytically. The step risks conflating exact NS specificity with usable NS specificity.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:74:The central gamble is that a small family of invariant tensor observables can meaningfully constrain the full pressure-Hessian contribution, including harmonic far-field freedom. That is a severe compression step, and the chain does not really justify why it should work beyond hopeful analogy.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:78:This branch lives directly next to existing work on strain-vorticity alignment, eigenvalue geometry, restricted Euler defects, pressure-Hessian modeling, and conditional regularity criteria. Novelty screening belongs before the observable shortlist becomes emotionally favored, not after.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:96:What is weak is the underlying bet: that one can distill enough of the pressure-coupled tensor dynamics into a robust observable to gain coercive control. That is precisely the compression that earlier tensor and pressure-structure routes have repeatedly failed to make decisive. The most credible output here is therefore not a proposition-scale regularity mechanism, but a sharper obstruction memo explaining why the pressure-Hessian route remains structurally informative and yet analytically nonclosing once the full nonlocal debt is paid.
